{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":13794,"record_hash":"sha256:33583be79c57e156609cf555e8a856cfbd6d5badcb429da8dc067be05b97ab9d","timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:19:59.376Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"<proposed_plan>\n# Agentlog Shareable Session Data Shape Plan\n\n## Summary\nReshape the POC so captured agent sessions are stored as durable, shareable-ready GitMeta data, while the command remains hidden, explicit-path only, project-targeted, and non-pushing/non-serializing.\n\nDo not use `meta:local:*` for the main session data. GitMeta treats `meta:local:*` as never serialized, so it is wrong for data intended to support handoff or colleague sharing. Use a `gitbutler:*` namespace instead, following GitMetaâ€™s key/serialization model.\n\nReferences: [GitMeta serialize filters](https://git-meta.com/spec/implementation/serialize-filters.html), [standard keys](https://git-meta.com/spec/implementation/standard-keys.html), [targets and keys](https://git-meta.com/spec/exchange-format/targets.html).\n\n## Key Changes\n- Add `agent-session-capture/future-use-cases.md` describing:\n  - Session handoff across machines and agents.\n  - Sharing session details with colleagues through a future GitButler web view.\n  - Access patterns: list sessions, inspect sources, read ordered records, generate handoff context.\n- Update existing docs to say:\n  - POC writes shareable-ready `gitbutler:*` keys, not `meta:local:*`.\n  - Capture still does not serialize, push, fetch, or sync GitMeta.\n  - All stored agentlog values are redacted before writing.\n  - Branch/PR/commit links are future references to durable project sessions.\n\n## Storage Shape\nUse the `project` GitMeta target by default.\n\nSession index:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n```\n\nDurable session prefix:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*\n```\n\nFor this POC, `session-key` is deterministic from the current source:\n\n```text\nsha256(agent + NUL + provider-session-id)\n```\n\nor, if no provider session id exists:\n\n```text\nsha256(agent + NUL + canonical-transcript-path-bytes)\n```\n\nSession-level keys:\n\n```text\n:schema = gitbutler.agent-session.v1\n:updated-at = <capture timestamp>\n:sources = set<source-key>\n:record-hashes = set<sha256:record>\n:transcript = list<TranscriptEnvelope JSON>\n```\n\nSource-level keys:\n\n```text\n:source:<source-key>:agent\n:source:<source-key>:provider\n:source:<source-key>:model\n:source:<source-key>:tool-version\n:source:<source-key>:provider-session-key\n:source:<source-key>:source-name\n:source:<source-key>:source-size\n:source:<source-key>:source-sha256\n:source:<source-key>:last-record-index\n:source:<source-key>:captured-at\n```\n\nDo not store full transcript paths, cwd, or git branch in this POC data shape. `source-name` is basename only. `provider-session-key` is hashed, never raw.\n\n## Transcript Envelope\nKeep one ordered `:transcript` list per durable GitButler session. Each list item is one redacted JSON envelope with only per-record data.\n\nEnvelope fields:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"schema\": \"gitbutler.agent-transcript.v1\",\n  \"source_key\": \"sha256-...\",\n  \"record_index\": 0,\n  \"record_hash\": \"sha256:...\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"...\",\n  \"event_kind\": \"...\",\n  \"event_category\": \"message\",\n  \"role\": \"user\",\n  \"content_text\": \"redacted normalized text when easy to extract\",\n  \"tool_name\": null,\n  \"source_record\": {}\n}\n```\n\nRules:\n- Omit repeated session/source metadata from each envelope; use `source_key` to join back to source keys.\n- Omit `cwd`, `git_branch`, provider session ids, message ids, parent ids, turn ids, and redaction counters from top-level envelope fields.\n- Keep redacted `source_record` for provenance and future normalization improvements.\n- `event_category`: `session`, `context`, `message`, `tool`, or `other`.\n- Codex content: extract only obvious string content/text fields.\n- Claude content: extract `message.content` string, or join text blocks from `message.content[]`.\n- `tool_name`: extract only obvious tool-name fields.\n- Redact every copied string field and the full `source_record` before writing.\n\n## Implementation Notes\n- Rename storage constants away from `meta:local:gitbutler:*` to `gitbutler:agent-session:*`.\n- Keep parser branches closed and explicit for Codex and Claude; no plugin framework.\n- Keep CLI unchanged:\n  - no `--session-id`\n  - no discovery\n  - no branch inference\n  - no serialize/push/sync\n- Keep dedupe behavior:\n  - `:record-hashes` tracks record-derived writes.\n  - transcript append dedupe is rebuilt from existing envelope `record_hash` values.\n  - duplicate records in one run append once.\n- Update tests/docs that assert old local-only keys or verbose envelope fields.\n\n## Test Plan\n- `cargo test -p but-agentlog`\n  - session index is written under `gitbutler:agent-sessions`\n  - session data is under `gitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*`\n  - no `meta:local:gitbutler:agent-session:*` keys are written\n  - source-level keys are written with basename-only `source-name`\n  - transcript envelopes contain only the slim per-record fields\n  - envelope `source_key` joins to source metadata\n  - repeat capture remains idempotent\n  - growing transcript appends only new records\n  - missing transcript list still backfills from existing record hashes\n  - redaction applies to source metadata, normalized envelope fields, and `source_record`\n- `cargo check -p but --features agentlog`\n- `cargo fmt --check`\n- `cargo clippy -p but-agentlog --all-targets --no-deps`\n\n## Assumptions\n- All stored agentlog data is intended to be shareable eventually, so all stored values must be redacted before saving.\n- The POC still does not actually share data because it does not call GitMeta serialize, push, fetch, or sync.\n- `project` remains the default target.\n- Branch, PR, commit, and website associations will later point to durable GitButler session ids.\n- Standard `agent:*` keys are deferred until there is an interoperability/publish contract; this POC uses `gitbutler:*`.\n</proposed_plan>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:19:59.376Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}